Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Trim the @butternut squash{1}, halve lengthways, then scoop out the seeds (peel
first if you prefer). Cut into 2cm chunks.

Pop the butternut onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{1%tbsp}, sprinkle
over the @mixed herbs{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to
coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast the butternut on the top shelf until golden and cooked
through, ~{18-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}.

Tear the @ciabatta{1} into roughly 2cm chunks.

Drain and tear the @mozzarella{1%ball}.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @pesto{32%g}, @red wine vinegar{12%ml},
@sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Pop the ciabatta onto a baking tray in a single layer. Drizzle with oil, season
with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

When everything's ready, add the tomatoes, roasted squash and croutons to the
dressing bowl. Toss to coat.

Just before serving, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} and toss to combine.

> TIP: Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy.

Share the salad between your #bowls{}.

Top with the mozzarella and sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}.

Drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} to finish.

Enjoy!